strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_diff_staged", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_diff", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"target": {"description": "target", "title": "Target", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["target"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_log", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"max_count": {"default": 10, "description": "max_count", "title": "Max Count", "type": "integer"}}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_show", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"revision": {"description": "revision", "title": "Revision", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["revision"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "transfer_to_qa", "description": "Forward to QA when the implementation is approved.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": true}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "transfer_to_engineer", "description": "Send back to the Engineer when issues need fixing.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": true}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "transfer_to_projectmanager", "description": "Escalate to the ProjectManager only for scope or business decisions.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": true}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are Dave, a Code Reviewer.\n\n## Mesh workflow\nYou sit between the Engineer and QA in the SDLC mesh:\n\n    Engineer \u2192 You \u2192 QA  (happy path)\n               You \u2192 Engineer  (issues found)\n\nMake the routing decision yourself based on review outcome \u2014 do not return\nto the ProjectManager.  Only escalate to the PM if you encounter a situation\nthat requires a business or scope decision you cannot resolve.\n\n## Your responsibilities\n- Inspect the implementation code and git diffs to evaluate correctness,\n  readability, maintainability, performance, and adherence to standards.\n- Use the knowledge base docs as reference for architecture and conventions.\n- Provide clear, actionable feedback with specific file/line references.\n- If critical issues are found, list them explicitly so the Engineer can\n  address them.\n- You will be given the ticket file path(s) on the project board (typically\n  under data/project_board/tickets/). Update the corresponding ticket file:\n  - If changes are acceptable, keep Status as IN REVIEW (QA will move it to DONE).\n  - If significant issues remain, move Status back to IN PROGRESS and clearly\n    state what must be fixed before handing back to the Engineer.\n- When passing off to QA, include: the ticket file path(s) and a summary of\n  what was reviewed and approved.\n- When sending back to the Engineer, include: the ticket file path(s) and a\n  clear, prioritised list of issues to fix.\n\n## Handoff tools available to you\n- transfer_to_QA             : forward to QA when the implementation is approved.\n- transfer_to_Engineer       : send back to the Engineer when issues need fixing.\n- transfer_to_ProjectManager : escalate to the PM only when a scope/business decision is needed.\n\n## Other tools available to you\n- board_*       : read and write the project board (data/project_board/).\n- docs_*        : read from the knowledge base (data/knowledge_base/).\n- code_read_*   : read the implementation code (data/workspace/).\n- git_*         : inspect diffs, commits, and branch state.\n\n## Rules\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT modify any code files.\n- Route to transfer_to_QA or transfer_to_Engineer based on review outcome;\n  use transfer_to_ProjectManager only for genuine escalations.\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a CLI Todo App with JSON"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-001-setup-structure.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-002-json-storage.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-003-cli-commands.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-004-data-validation.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-005-user-documentation.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/index.md"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "I have successfully created the tickets for the CLI Todo App and updated the project board index. Here\u2019s a summary of the tickets created:\n\n1. **T-20231006-001** - Setup Project Structure  \n   - **Status**: TO DO  \n   - **Owner**: Engineer  \n\n2. **T-20231006-002** - JSON File Storage Implementation  \n   - **Status**: TO DO  \n   - **Owner**: Engineer  \n\n3. **T-20231006-003** - CLI Command Implementation  \n   - **Status**: TO DO  \n   - **Owner**: Engineer  \n\n4. **T-20231006-004** - Data Validation  \n   - **Status**: TO DO  \n   - **Owner**: Engineer  \n\n5. **T-20231006-005** - User Documentation  \n   - **Status**: TO DO  \n   - **Owner**: Engineer  \n\nThe project board index has also been updated to reflect these ticket entries. \n\nNext steps include delegating the setup of the project structure to the Engineer to kick off the work. I will proceed with that now."}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Transferred to Engineer, adopting the role of Engineer immediately."}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "ID: T-20231006-001\nTitle: Setup Project Structure\nStatus: TO DO\nOwner: Engineer\nDescription: Create the basic directory structure for the CLI Todo app.\nAcceptance Criteria:\n- Project directories are created (src, tests, etc.).\n- Basic README file exists.\n- Initial package.json is created.\nTasks:\n- [ ] Create 'src' directory.\n- [ ] Create 'tests' directory.\n- [ ] Initialize a package.json file.\nLinks: N/A\nUpdates / History: Initial ticket created."}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/src\nSuccessfully created directory data/workspace/tests\nSuccessfully wrote to data/workspace/README.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/workspace/package.json"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-001-setup-structure.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Transferred to CodeReviewer, adopting the role of CodeReviewer immediately."}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-DKK157yysT9MY8nWKYY7fb8t3xYZh", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": null, "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_szDafOSUIFR8Ff84bwCgLA0z", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-001-setup-structure.md\"}", "name": "board_read_file"}, "type": "function"}]}}], "created": 1773735875, "model": "gpt-4o-mini-2024-07-18", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "default", "system_fingerprint": "fp_01e9202de8", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 31, "prompt_tokens": 1762, "total_tokens": 1793, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 0}}}, "prompt_tokens": 1762, "completion_tokens": 31, "agent_id": "CodeReviewer_bbc7ebc5-2e1c-431b-899