"code_create_directory", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "code_move_file", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"source": {"description": "source", "title": "Source", "type": "string"}, "destination": {"description": "destination", "title": "Destination", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["source", "destination"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "transfer_to_projectmanager", "description": "Report completion to the ProjectManager when all tests pass.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": true}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "transfer_to_engineer", "description": "Send bugs directly to the Engineer when issues are found.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": true}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are Eve, a QA Engineer.\n\n## Mesh workflow\nYou are the last specialist in the SDLC mesh before the ProjectManager:\n\n    CodeReviewer \u2192 You \u2192 ProjectManager  (all clear)\n                   You \u2192 Engineer        (bugs found)\n\nMake the routing decision yourself based on test results \u2014 you do not need\nthe PM to relay the decision.\n\n## Your responsibilities\n- Inspect the project board and the implemented code to understand what\n  should be tested.\n- Design test cases covering happy paths, edge cases, and regressions.\n- Document your test results clearly, listing any failures or quality concerns.\n- You will be given the ticket file path(s) on the project board (typically\n  under data/project_board/tickets/). When you finish validating a ticket,\n  add a brief summary of test results to that ticket file and make sure the\n  Status accurately reflects whether the work is DONE or needs further changes.\n- When sending bugs back to the Engineer, include: the ticket file path(s)\n  and a clear, prioritised list of failures with reproduction steps.\n- When all tests pass, move ticket Status to DONE and report back to the PM.\n\n## Handoff tools available to you\n- transfer_to_ProjectManager : report completion to the PM when all tests pass.\n- transfer_to_Engineer       : send bugs directly to the Engineer when issues are found.\n\n## Other tools available to you\n- board_*       : read and write the project board (data/project_board/).\n- code_read_*   : read the implementation code (data/workspace/).\n\n## Rules\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT modify implementation code.\n- Route to transfer_to_Engineer when bugs are found; use transfer_to_ProjectManager\n  only when all tests pass (or for genuine escalations).\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a CLI Todo App with JSON"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-001-setup-structure.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-002-json-storage.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-003-cli-commands.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-004-data-validation.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-005-user-documentation.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/index.md"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "I have successfully created the tickets for the CLI Todo App and updated the project board index. Here\u2019s a summary of the tickets created:\n\n1. **T-20231006-001** - Setup Project Structure  \n   - **Status**: TO DO  \n   - **Owner**: Engineer  \n\n2. **T-20231006-002** - JSON File Storage Implementation  \n   - **Status**: TO DO  \n   - **Owner**: Engineer  \n\n3. **T-20231006-003** - CLI Command Implementation  \n   - **Status**: TO DO  \n   - **Owner**: Engineer  \n\n4. **T-20231006-004** - Data Validation  \n   - **Status**: TO DO  \n   - **Owner**: Engineer  \n\n5. **T-20231006-005** - User Documentation  \n   - **Status**: TO DO  \n   - **Owner**: Engineer  \n\nThe project board index has also been updated to reflect these ticket entries. \n\nNext steps include delegating the setup of the project structure to the Engineer to kick off the work. I will proceed with that now."}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Transferred to Engineer, adopting the role of Engineer immediately."}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "ID: T-20231006-001\nTitle: Setup Project Structure\nStatus: TO DO\nOwner: Engineer\nDescription: Create the basic directory structure for the CLI Todo app.\nAcceptance Criteria:\n- Project directories are created (src, tests, etc.).\n- Basic README file exists.\n- Initial package.json is created.\nTasks:\n- [ ] Create 'src' directory.\n- [ ] Create 'tests' directory.\n- [ ] Initialize a package.json file.\nLinks: N/A\nUpdates / History: Initial ticket created."}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/src\nSuccessfully created directory data/workspace/tests\nSuccessfully wrote to data/workspace/README.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/workspace/package.json"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/tickets/T-20231006-001-setup-structure.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Transferred to CodeReviewer, adopting the role of CodeReviewer immediately."}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "ID: T-20231006-001\nTitle: Setup Project Structure\nStatus: IN PROGRESS\nOwner: Engineer\nDescription: Create the basic directory structure for the CLI Todo ap